<item>
            <title>[SPARK-15978] Some improvement of &quot;Show Tables&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15978</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve found some minor issues in &quot;show tables&quot; command:&lt;br/&gt;
1. In the SessionCatalog.scala, listTables(db: String) method will call listTables(formatDatabaseName(db), &quot;*&quot;) to list all the tables for certain db, but in the method listTables(db: String, pattern: String), this db name is formatted once more. So I think we should remove formatDatabaseName() in the caller.&lt;br/&gt;
2. I suggest to add sort to listTables(db: String) in InMemoryCatalog.scala, just like listDatabases().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will make a PR shortly. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
